23/01/2007
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The government has made significant progress in key reforms and the new government is implementing them at much faster pace than the previous one, Bruce Courtney, head of a World Bank Mission to Skopje, said on Monday (January 22nd). 
The Bank team is in the country to assess the Second Programme Development Policies Loan, under which Macedonia hopes to receive some $30m. 
(Vecer - 23/01/07; Makfax - 22/01/07)
